class Solution {
public:
    int minimumOperationsToMakeEqual(int x, int y) {
        int diff = abs(x - y);
        int operations = 0;
        while (diff > 0) {
            if (diff % 11 == 0) {
                diff /= 11;
            } else if (diff % 5 == 0) {
                diff /= 5;
            } else {
                diff--;
            }
            operations++;
        }
        return operations;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(D) where D is the absolute difference between x and y
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iteratively reduces the absolute difference between x and y using the available operations. It prioritizes division by 11 and 5 when possible, as these operations lead to larger reductions in the difference.  Decrementing x is used as a last resort. This approach ensures that the minimum number of operations is used to achieve equality.

